''Margaritaville Cafe: Late Night Live'' was recorded live at Margaritaville Cafe in New Orleans, Louisiana, and was released in 2000 on [[Mailboat Records|Mailboat]] 2001 with a running time of 64:28. It is credited to Club Trini which includes Robert Greenridge (steel drums) and Michael Utley (keyboards) as well as Peter Mayer (vocals, guitar), [[Nadirah Shakoor]] (vocals), Jim Mayer (bass, background vocals), Roger Guth (drums), [[Ralph MacDonald]] (percussion), all members of Jimmy Buffett's [[Coral Reefer Band]]. Buffett himself sang and played guitar on some tracks as well. The album was produced by Utley and Greenridge.
